## 1. Purpose and Scope

This License Agreement (the "Agreement") governs your use of the software known
as "Foundation" and all accompanying source code, documentation, schema
configurations, benchmark records, practice controls, and scaffolding scripts
(collectively, the "Software") owned by OVASABI STUDIOS LTD ("Licensor").

By using, copying, modifying, or distributing the Software, you accept the
terms of this Agreement.

## 2. Definitions

- **"Commercial Purpose"** means use of the Software to run, support, or enable
  a product, service, or internal system of a for-profit business, or any use
  intended for commercial advantage or monetary compensation.
- **"Organization"** means you together with all entities that control you, are
  controlled by you, or are under common control with you, with revenue and
  funding measured on a consolidated group basis.
- **"Revenue Threshold"** means (a) more than US $1,000,000 in gross revenue in
  the most recent twelve (12) month period, or (b) more than US $1,000,000 in
  total financing raised (equity, debt, grants, or token sales combined).
- **"AI System"** means any machine learning model, neural network, or
  artificial intelligence system, including code-generation and
  software-synthesis models.
- **"Training Use"** means any use of the Software, in whole or in part, where
  the purpose or effect is to create, train, fine-tune, align, evaluate for
  development purposes, distill, or otherwise improve an AI System — including
  use as training data, fine-tuning data, reinforcement-learning data
  (RLHF/RLAIF or similar), distillation source material, embedding corpora
  assembled for model training, or seed material for synthetic training data.
- **"Inference Use"** means providing the Software as contextual input to an
  AI System at inference time for the purpose of developing, maintaining,
  reviewing, testing, documenting, or operating software — including use of AI
  coding assistants and autonomous coding agents operating on the Software.

## 3. License Grant (Community Use)

Subject to the restrictions in Section 4, Licensor grants you a worldwide,
royalty-free, non-exclusive, non-sublicensable, non-transferable license to
use, copy, modify, and distribute the Software for:

1. **Non-commercial purposes**, including personal projects, research, and
   education;
2. **Open-source development**, provided that any derivative work or
   application utilizing the Software is published under a license approved by
   the Open Source Initiative (OSI); and
3. **Commercial Purposes, only while your Organization does not exceed the
   Revenue Threshold.**

For the scope of these permitted uses, the terms and permissions of the
**Apache License 2.0** are incorporated into this Agreement by reference. Where
this Agreement and the Apache License 2.0 conflict, this Agreement controls.

## 4. Restrictions

### 4.1. Commercial Use Above the Revenue Threshold

If your Organization exceeds the Revenue Threshold, you may not use the
Software or any derivative work of the Software for any Commercial Purpose
without a separate written commercial license agreement from OVASABI STUDIOS
LTD. Community use under Sections 3.1 and 3.2 remains permitted.

If your Organization crosses the Revenue Threshold while using the Software
commercially, you must obtain a commercial license within ninety (90) days of
crossing it.

### 4.2. AI Training Exclusion

**Training Use of the Software is prohibited.** This restriction applies
regardless of whether your use of the AI System or the resulting model is
commercial or non-commercial, and regardless of your Organization's size.

**Inference Use is expressly permitted** and does not constitute Training Use,
provided that you do not knowingly grant the AI System's provider rights to
retain or use the Software for Training Use (for example, by submitting the
Software through service tiers whose terms permit training on user content
where an opt-out or non-training tier is reasonably available).

For the avoidance of doubt: building retrieval indexes or embeddings over the
Software solely to assist Inference Use is permitted; contributing the Software
or such derivatives to any corpus used to create or improve an AI System is
not.

## 5. Obtaining a Commercial License

Commercial licenses are offered in tiers aligned to deployment posture:

- **Commercial** — for Organizations above the Revenue Threshold using the
  Software for Commercial Purposes.
- **Enterprise / Sovereign** — fully self-hosted or air-gapped deployment with
  offline license verification (signed license file), private registry access,
  and contractual data-sovereignty and IP warranties for regulated
  environments.
- **Training Rights** — any Training Use under Section 4.2, licensed
  separately and only by express written agreement.

To obtain a commercial license, contact:

- **Email:** <licensing@ovasabi.studio>
- **Company:** OVASABI STUDIOS LTD
- **Company Registration No:** 7357449 (Federal Republic of Nigeria)

## 5A. Data Sovereignty Covenant

Licensor commits, for all use under this Agreement, that:

1. The Software as distributed by Licensor contains no telemetry and performs
   no network transmission of your source code, schemas, prompts, tenant data,
   or derivative works to Licensor or any third party.
2. License verification is available fully offline; no license check requires
   sending Licensor anything beyond license credentials, and air-gapped
   operation is a supported mode, not an exception.
3. Licensor claims no ownership over applications, domain schemas, or other
   works you build using the Software. Your business logic is yours.

